HEADWORD: cigarfish
<hw>cigarfish</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>a small fusiform fish (<spn>Decapterus
punctatus</spn>), allied to the mackerel, found in the West Atlantic and
on the coast of the Gulf of Mexico.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> round scad, quiaquia, Decapterus
punctatus.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cigarillo</ent>⟦br⟧
